A man came running from the far side of the city, saying: "O Moses, the commanders are plotting to kill you, so leave immediately. I am giving you good advice."
He exited the city, afraid and watchful. He said, "My Lord, save me from the wicked people."
As he traveled towards Midyan, he said, "Perhaps my Lord will guide me to the right path."
